# The error message `Could_not_find_a_nearby_entity_to_insert_into` suggests that there is no entity nearby to insert the item into. You can try moving closer to an entity which can accept items or placing an entity that can accept the item closer to you for easier insertion. 
For example, you can add the following code snippet before the inventory check to place a new chest closer to you if there is no iron chest nearby:
```python
    if 'iron-chest' not in {e['name'] for e in entities}:
        move_to((-10, -10), laying='transport-belt')
        place_entity('iron-chest', position=current_position())
        move_to(nearest('iron-ore'), laying='transport-belt')
        # If there is no iron chest on the map, move to (-10, -10), place an iron chest, and then move to the nearest iron ore resource.
```
If there are no nearby iron chests, this code will move you to (-10,-10), place an iron chest, and then move you to the nearest iron ore resource. If there is already an iron chest nearby, the code will be skipped and the game will proceed with the main logic.
